            <biogHist> 
                <abstract>Elisa Servenius, née Bernström, also known as Johanna Servenius (fl. 1810), was a woman who served in the Swedish army dressed as a man during the Finnish War between Sweden and Russia 1808-1809. She was decorated for bravery in battle, and was the first and only woman in Sweden awarded the För tapperhet i fält for bravery in battle on land, while Brita Hagberg and Anna Maria Engsten were decorated for bravery at sea.</abstract>
                <citation>Wikipedia. "Elisa Servenius" Accessed February 19, 2020. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elisa_Servenius</citation>
